---
description: Every service method must emit structured logs, a Prometheus metric, and capture errors in Sentry
globs: ["signal-lab/apps/api/src/**/*.service.ts"]
alwaysApply: true
---

# Observability — Three Pillars Required

Any service method that touches the DB, calls external services, or runs business logic
MUST implement all three pillars before the code is considered complete.

---

## Pillar 1 — Structured logs (→ Loki)

Log objects, never strings. Always include an `event` field.

```ts
// ✅ DO — object with event field
this.logger.log({ event: 'scenario_started', scenario: name, runId: run.id });
this.logger.log({ event: 'scenario_completed', scenario: name, runId: run.id, metric });
this.logger.error({ event: 'scenario_failed', scenario: name, runId: run.id, error: message });

// ❌ DON'T — plain string (unparseable in Loki)
this.logger.log('scenario started');
this.logger.log(`running ${name}`);
```

Required events per method:
- `[resource]_[action]_start` — on entry
- `[resource]_[action]_success` — on completion
- `[resource]_[action]_failed` — in catch block

---

## Pillar 2 — Prometheus metrics (→ Grafana)

Every significant operation needs a counter. Duration-sensitive ops need a histogram.

```ts
// ✅ DO — counter on both paths
this.metrics.scenarioCounter.inc({ scenario: name, status: 'completed' });

// ✅ DO — histogram for duration
const end = this.metrics.scenarioDuration.startTimer({ scenario: name });
try {
  // ... work ...
  end();
} catch (err) {
  end();
  throw err;
}

// ❌ DON'T — no metric emitted at all
async create(dto: CreateScenarioDto) {
  return this.prisma.scenarioRun.create({ data: dto }); // silent — Prometheus sees nothing
}
```

---

## Pillar 3 — Error tracking (→ Sentry)

Every catch block that handles a real error MUST call `Sentry.captureException`.
Always attach `tags` (for filtering) and `extra` (for context).

```ts
// ✅ DO
} catch (err) {
  const message = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);
  this.logger.error({ event: 'scenario_failed', scenario: name, error: message });
  Sentry.captureException(err, {
    tags: { scenario: name },
    extra: { runId: run.id },
  });
  throw err;  // or rethrow as InternalServerErrorException
}

// ❌ DON'T — swallowed error, Sentry never notified
} catch (err) {
  this.logger.error('something failed');
}

// ❌ DON'T — Sentry called without context
} catch (err) {
  Sentry.captureException(err);  // no tags = unfilterable in Sentry dashboard
}
```

---

## Self-check before marking a method done

- [ ] `logger.log({ event: '..._start', ... })` at method entry
- [ ] `logger.log({ event: '..._success', ... })` on happy path
- [ ] `logger.error({ event: '..._failed', ... })` in catch
- [ ] `metrics.[counter].inc({ ..., status })` on both paths
- [ ] `Sentry.captureException(err, { tags, extra })` in catch
